Caml programmers!

This is just to remind you that the

	Journal of Functional Programming

is always on the look out for good papers.  JFP publishes papers on 

	theory of all sorts, 
		including the Theoretical Pearls column
	implementation, 
	programming techniques, 
		including the Programming Pearls column
	algorithms 
		see Chris Okasaki's call for papers for a special issue
		http://www.dcs.gla.ac.uk/jfp/editorialAugust99.html,
	libraries and toolkits,
	foreign language integration,
	programming evironments, 
	and applications

and more besides.  Consult any of the editors personally if you'd like
advice about whether an idea you have in mind is suitable.  You'll
find details about past issues, submission information, and more at

		     http://www.dcs.gla.ac.uk/jfp

Simon Peyton Jones
Phil Wadler
Paul Hudak
Thierry Coquand
